%S A395553 1,4,7,12,20,30,42,58,77,100,127,158,194,236,282,334,393,458,529,608,
%T A395553 694,788,890,1000,1119,1248,1385,1532,1690,1858,2036,2226,2427,2640,
%U A395553 2865,3102,3352,3616,3892,4182,4487,4806,5139,5488,5852,6232,6628
%N A395553 Number of no-overhang stacked partitions (teeth) of base 4 and total size n.
%C A395553 A tooth of base r is a finite stack of rows of unit cubes with bottom row of length r, weakly decreasing row lengths, and no row overhanging the row beneath it. This sequence is row r=4 of the triangle A395557.
%D A395553 Paul M. King, Generating Functions for Temperley's No-Overhang Stacked Partitions, Journal of Integer Sequences (submitted).
%H A395553 <a href="/index/Rec#order_10">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1,1,0,0,-2,0,0,1,1,-1).
%F A395553 G.f.: h_4(q) = q^4*(1+q)*(1+2q+q^3)/((1-q)*(1-q^2)*(1-q^3)*(1-q^4)).
%F A395553 T(4,N) = [q^N] h_4(q) where h_r(q) satisfies (1-q^r)*h_r(q) = 2q*h_{r-1}(q) - q^2*h_{r-2}(q), with h_0(q)=1 and h_1(q)=q/(1-q).
%Y A395553 Row r=4 of A395557. Next row: A395554 (r=5). Other rows: A000012 (r=1), A001477 (r=2), A000212 (r=3, with offset).
%K A395553 nonn,easy,new
%O A395553 4,2
